Usage: createRouteBlkAlongTrack [-help] -align_track <string>
                                [-consider_cells_as_macros <string>]
                                [-consider_macros_as_cells <string>]
                                [-edge_shrink {x y}] -layer <string>
                                [-no_cut_row]

-help                                  # Prints out the command usage
-align_track <string>                  # Specify layer track which route
                                       # blockages align to. (string, required)
-consider_cells_as_macros <string>     # Specify cell names which tool takes
                                       # them as macros. Blockages will not be
                                       # created over them. (string, optional)
-consider_macros_as_cells <string>     # Specify cell names which tool takes
                                       # them as std cells. Blockages will be
                                       # created over them. (string, optional)
-edge_shrink {x y}                     # Shrink row area from edge in X and Y
                                       # direction. (point, optional)
-layer <string>                        # Specify layer name to create route
                                       # blockages for stream out.
                                       # (string, required)
-no_cut_row                            # Specify whether add blockage based on
                                       # cut row site area even though row site
                                       # area isn't cut in design (bool, optional)